# VRMXT Plugin for Warudo repository

- Target Unity `2021.3.45f2`; do not silently raise Unity, package, API compatibility,
  or C# language requirements.
- Keep **Api Compatibility Level** at `.NET Framework` (`apiCompatibilityLevel: 3`).
  Warudo Mod Tool needs Framework Reflection.Emit APIs; `.NET Standard 2.1` breaks it.
- Keep **Assembly Version Validation** unchecked (`assemblyVersionValidation: 0`)
  per Warudo SDK install docs.
- Keep first-party plugin code under `Assets/` (or a local UPM package under `Packages/`
  if one is introduced). Prefer `Runtime`, `Editor`, `Tests`, and samples folders that
  match nearby Warudo/VRMXT conventions.
- Select namespace and dependencies from nearby code and the nearest `.asmdef`.
  There is no single repository root namespace.
- Runtime assemblies must not reference Editor assemblies or `UnityEditor`.
  Put editor-only code under an `Editor` folder and editor-only asmdef.
- When crossing an assembly boundary, update the owning `.asmdef` deliberately.
  Avoid adding broad or circular references.
- Preserve Warudo plugin load behavior, serialized data, and public API compatibility.
  Avoid unrelated cleanup in legacy files.
- Do not edit vendored or embedded UniVRM/VRMXT package trees as if they were first-party
  sources when an upstream or sibling repo owns them; identify the owning source first.

## Plugin version bumps

When asked to update / increment the plugin version, bump **all** of these that exist
(keep them equal):

- Plugin `[Plugin]` / assembly `Version` attribute (e.g. `Assets/Vrmxt/Scripts/VrmxtPlugin.cs`)
- `umod/ExportSettings.example.asset` → primary mod profile `modVersion`
- Live `Assets/ExportSettings.asset` → same `modVersion` (gitignored; still update if present)
- Backup `umod/local/ExportSettings.asset.old` → same `modVersion` when the file exists

Restoring from `.old` must not silently roll the version back. Prefer editing `.old`
alongside the live file, or run `.\umod\export-settings.ps1 -Backup` after a correct bump.
